ched the  flight hour milestone on its fleet of aws in australia more news careers join the thousands of experienced and talented people around the globe who work at chc search careers  safety  quality summit register now chc helicopter is proud to supportthe ihst safety initiative careers  chc  infochchelicom facebook twitter linkedin youtube companyour story leadership history press releases purpose and values fleet our code of ethics globalregions safety  innovationsafety innovation solutionsoffshore transport sar  ems mro training careers an exceptional combination of talent passion and experience nbsp go to schedules search flight schedule select the flight date arrivals or departures and a heliport then click get schedule skip to main content   at chc our greatest strength is our people – an experienced talented and committed team certified and trained to the highest industry standards they are differencemakers dedicated to getting our customers where they need to be when they need to be there anywhere in the world – safely and reliably that is why we look for only the best talent to help our business reach beyond challenges and deliver for our customers at chc our strong ethical values integrity and clearlydefined standards for accountability have guided our actions for  years we are committed to cultivating an environment where open transparent and honest communication is the expectation not the exception our team strives to deliver outstanding customer service anywhere in the world whether it’s through flight operations maintenance passenger service or other functions we offer worldrenowned driven by a professional operational infrastructure that reduces risk in all respects our global team of experts manages our fleet and utilizes innovative technology to provide tailored solutions for our customers with global operations supported by localized knowhow we can respond quickly efficiently and safely to meet any customer need we provide our customers with customized oil and gas transport solutions while also providing search and rescue and emergency medical service to both private and government customers throughout the world each year we carry millions of passengers to their destinations safely and reliably on six continents in all types of environments we also provide essential search and rescue and emergency medical capabilities to help save lives throughout the world from the highlytrained flight crew to the engineers and maintenance teams that support them at each stop our people make the difference we rely on a global logistics and engineering team that efficiently plans and tailors whatever resources are needed to support aroundtheclock operations we know the best people become even more effective when they are continually provided with innovative technology from a global supply chain management system to global aircraﬅ monitoring to a shared digital records library we make sure that our teams can get what they need quickly to keep things running smoothly for our customers all of this is supported at our corporate headquarters and global operations center in dallas texas where we help accelerate the integration of advanced tools systems and processes for specific flightoperations support maintenance and technicalsupport functions every day around the clock we are looking for people who can not only utilize these systems but help us continue to evolve and push the boundaries of innovation in our industry if you’re a go getter and problemsolver and are interested in joining a team dedicated to quickly mobilizing customer solutions for a global customer base then chc wants to talk to you we offer challenging opportunities to learn and grow so you can reach beyond to achieve your career goals check out our current openings and apply today   careers contact us press releases ethics privacy policy offshore transport services  chc helicopter menu flight schedule what we do offshore transport flight schedule search  rescue sar emergency medical services ems helione mro services flight training offshore expertise that runs wide  deep decades of overwater flying in extremely demanding conditions have honed unmatched knowledge skill—and leadership—in offshore transportation for companies that discover and produce oil and natural gas each year our people carry more than one million passengers to and from the ships and platforms that make up their offshore workplaces today deepwater and ultradeepwater reserves represent the vast majority of the worlds new oil and gas discoveries overwhelmingly in places where we have wellestablished capabilities off the coasts of australia brazil norway the united kingdom and several nations in africa as our customers continue to go further to explore and produce oil and gas chcs worldclass advanced fleet innovative technology and global reach make us uniquely able to understand and safely meet their needs irweblink thank you for your interest in ir solutions you have reached this page because the url you have requested is no longer available or you do not have permission to view it for more information on the most comprehensive ir web site management tool available please click here if you have any questions email irsupportsnlcom or call   and ask for an ir solutions sales representative please click here to return to the main snl financial homepage   unauthorized access chc helicopter  wikipedia chc helicopter from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from chcscotia jump to navigation search this article relies too much on references to primary sources please improve this by adding secondary or tertiary sources january  learn how and when to remove this template message chc helicopter  further more home safely  type public traded as nyse heli industry transportation predecessor sealand helicopters okanagan air services viking helicopters successor canadian helicopters founded st johns newfoundland  founder craig dobbin carl agar okanagan air services headquarters richmond british columbia canada area served worldwide key people karl fessenden ceo lee eckert cfo services helicopter services revenue us billion  number of employees   subsidiaries helione website wwwchcca chc helicopter is a large helicopter services company specializing in the following services transportation to offshore oil and gas platforms civilian search and rescue and air medical evacuation services helicopter maintenance repair and overhaul chc helicopter is headquartered in richmond british columbia canada and operates more than  aircraft in  countries around the world chcs major international operating units are based in australia brazil ireland the netherlands norway and the united kingdom the company is one of several global providers of helicopter transportation services to the offshore oil and gas industry others including bristow helicopters and nhv chc has capabilities in precision flying techniques and technical supportclarification needed chc has longterm working relationships with most of the major oil and gas companies chc operates the marine search and rescue service for the irish coast guard at shannon waterford sligo and dublin airports and provides commercial search and rescue helicopter services for the united kingdom maritime and coastguard agency chc provides helicopter services in australia for the fire and emergency services authority of western australia victoria police and the ambulance service of new south wales contents  history  divisions  chc ems and sar services  ireland  united kingdom  australia  military  police  ambulance  norway  other related services  fleet  helicopters  locations  accidents and incidents  see also  references  external links historyedit a eurocopter super puma in sealand helicopters livery a sikorsky s in okanagan helicopters livery commercial helicopter flying began in british columbia in the summer of  three exrcaf officers pilots carl agar and barney bent and engineer alf stringer were operating a fixedwing charter company okanagan air services ltd from penticton in july  they raised enough money to purchase a bell b and pay for their flying and maintenance training okanagan air services moved to vancouver in  renamed okanagan helicopters ltd by  it had become the largest commercial helicopter operator in the worldcitation needed in  newfoundland businessman craig dobbin headed a group of investors organized under the name canadian holding company and using the acronym chc chc purchased okanagan helicopters viking helicopters and toronto helicopters and merged them with dobbins own company sealand helicopters to form a company named canadian helicopters the parent company was renamed chc helicopter corporation chc acquired british international helicopters in  helicopter services group of norway in  including bond helicopters helikopter service as lloyd helicopters of australia and court helicopters of south africa in  chc purchased schreiner aviation group who provided offshore helicopter services in the dutch sector of the north sea and to the nigerian offshore industry in  chc entered into an agreement with fonds de solidarité ftq fstq and the management of its two canadian divisions canadian helicopters eastern and canadian helicopters western for the sale of an interest in chcs canadian assets in a management buyout to form canadian helicopters as a result senior management and fstq acquired  and  equity interests in canadian helicopters respectively while chc retained a  equity interest chc restructuring in  saw the creation of a new corporate headquarters in richmond british columbia and the creation of three main operating segments chc global operations based in richmond bc chc european operations based in aberdeen scotland and helione chcs leasing and repair and overhaul support group now based in delta bc in february  all of chcs shares were purchased by first reserve a us private equity company for cad billion  billion at the time the word corporation was dropped from the companys name which is now simply chc helicopter on january   chc announced an initial public offering of  shares first reserve now holds  of chcs shares on th jan  chc offered  shares at us on  may  chc helicopters filed for chapter  bankruptcy chc shares dropped from us th nov  to us cents  june  a texas court allowed chc in july  to shed  helicopters from its financial obligations most of the super pumas chc reorganized in march  divisionsedit chc manages its global operations through the following divisions eea helicopter operations bv eea a dutch company majority owned by eho holdings sarl and minority owned by chc helicopter sarl provides helicopter services in the north sea eea operates under the chc brand name and uses chc logo under licence it provides services from  bases in the uk ireland denmark norway and the netherlands brazilian helicopter services bhs brazil chc helicopters global operationscorporate office richmond british columbia chc helicopters australia chc helicopters africa chc composites gander newfoundland chc ems and sar servicesedit irelandedit chc s operated for the irish coast guard chc helicopter serves as the sole provider of search and rescue helicopter services to the irish coast guard where it had operated a fleet of six sikorsky sn helicopters based in dublin shannon waterford and sligo this fleet has now been replaced by  sikorsky s helibus the sn exited service in december  with a flight from dublin airport to weston aerodrome west dublin the flight was operated by eisar the oldest sn in commercial operation at the time united kingdomedit chc currently provides sar helicopters to two of the four maritime and coastguard agency bases in the uk portland leeonsolent and until recently also operated from sumburgh and stornoway chc as part of the soteria sar consortium was selected as the preferred bidder for a year contract to provide a civilian search and rescue service throughout the united kingdom however days before the contract was due to be signed in february  the british government halted the process after chc disclosed that it had unauthorised access to commercially sensitive information australiaedit chc is the largest provider of emergency medical helicopter services in australiacitation needed militaryedit royal australian air force raaf  chc has been providing dedicated rescue support to the raaf since  where it operates sikorsky s policeedit victoria police air wing and air ambulance services  chc provides three eurocopter san dauphin and one eurocopter ec aircraft plus maintenance services to the victoria police ambulanceedit snowy hydro southcare multipurpose helicopter in australia fire and emergency services authority of western australia  based in perth wa chc provides a bell  ep aircraft ambulance victoria  up until the end of  chc provided two bell ep helicopters for air ambulance and search and rescue duties ambulance service of new south wales  chc provides three aws and two ec helicopters to supplement ambulance nsws eight contracted aeromedical helicopters these are based at wollongong sydney and orange new south wales snowy hydro southcare air ambulance service  chc operates a bell  for emergency helicopter service based in symonston australian capital territory norwayedit norwegian search and rescue  chc provides private search and rescue services in the norwegian sector of the north sea but acts in concert with the norwegian rescue coordination centres the chc sar fleet includes two super puma l and three super puma ec  other related servicesedit nh chc is designing manufacturing and installing  liferaft assembly kits for the nh helicopter a new military search and rescue helicopter provided to the military of several european countries through a joint venture shared by agusta eurocopter and fokker supply rescue and support services chc provides extensive ship supply and rescue service off the coast of africa and the netherlands and helicopter support services to scientific expeditions in antarctica and other harsh environments fleetedit chc operates approximately  aircraft in over  countries which include malaysia australia brazil thailand the philippines the middle east south africa ecuador angola gabon and equatorial guinea helicoptersedit   agustawestland aw   eurocopter super puma as l l   eurocopter ec   eurocopter as n n n dauphin   sikorsky s a and c series   sikorsky s   bell    airbus ec  locationsedit  australia new south wales sydney • orange • wollongong • newcastle victoria melbourne • latrobe valley • bendigo western australia perth • karratha • broome  bangladesh  brazil  canada british columbia richmond delta nova scotia halifax  denmark esbjerg  india  indonesia  ireland cork • dublin • shannon • waterford • sligo  malaysia  norway stavanger • bergen • florø • kristiansund • brønnøysund  netherlands den helder  philippines  scotland • aberdeen • sumburgh  thailand  united kingdom • norwich • humberside accidents and incidentsedit on march   chc sikorsky s operating as rescue  crashed into the sea off blacksod west of ireland  fatalities  missing on april   a chc ec crashed near turøy norway killing all  occupants on august   a chc super puma l crashed  nm from sumburgh in the shetlands scotland the aircraft crashed into the sea killing  passengers and the remaining  passengers and  crew were rescued see alsoedit  chc helicopters eurocopter as crash canadian helicopters chc airways referencesedit  chc group reports fourth quarter and full year  resultsaccessdate   company profile for chc helicopter corp heli retrieved    helicopter firm chc group files for bankruptcy protection cbc news  may  retrieved  june    httpswwwflightglobalcomnewsarticlesmorebadnewsforairbushelicopterssuperpumafami  httpwwwchchelicomnode  httpwwwchccacorporateaboutchcphp  httpwwwairlinersnetphoto  press release soteria sar  february  retrieved  april    uk government shelves helicopter search a